docs/reviews/codex-2026-07-06-pub-slice-raw.md:2880:docs/reviews/codex-2026-07-03-m1-wedge-batch-raw.md:3:[P1] `bin/check.mjs:87` — `--conformance` wins over `--against`, so mixed-mode commands silently skip the truth leg — this matters because the headline exhibit is explicitly conformant but false (`evals/packs/ucp-conformance.test.ts:145`) — failure scenario: `check conformant-but-false.json --conformance --against sor.catalog.json` exits clean on schema shape while never checking the SOR lie — suggested fix: make `--conformance` mutually exclusive with `--against`/`--surface`, exit `2`, and add a regression using `conformant-but-false.json`.
