     1	# Suggestions Ledger — Claude's Independent Judgment
     2	
     3	**What this is:** the standing record of every independent suggestion Claude offers under the owner's judgment license (owner directive 2026-07-02: "till we proceed to build give independent judgement, add your suggestions"). Nothing lives only in chat — every suggestion lands here with its status. The owner disposes; the plan-stage gates (council → Codex → owner GO) ratify anything consequential.
     4	
     5	**Statuses:** `ACCEPTED` (owner accepted; recorded in decision-log) · `ACCEPTED-FOR-PLANNING` (accepted as the working direction; final ratification at the plan-stage gates) · `PENDING` (awaiting owner reaction — fold into the plan surfaced for GO) · `PROPOSED` (new; not yet reacted to).
     6	
     7	| ID | Date | Suggestion | Why (one line) | Status |
     8	| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
     9	| S-1 | 2026-07-02 | **Reframe UC-2's lead artifact: an OPEN ACP/UCP conformance + truth-audit toolkit** ("the truth layer for agentic commerce") instead of a merchant-facing prototype SaaS; UC-7 (feed-conformance tooling) promoted from horizon into the lead artifact. | Makes "adoption-grade" literally achievable (the ecosystem can run it), deletes the surface-access/ToS killer, rides the open ACP/UCP timing window (specs weeks old, conformance seat empty), flips spec churn from risk to moat. | ACCEPTED-FOR-PLANNING (decision-log 2026-07-02) |
    10	| S-2 | 2026-07-02 | **The self-referential demo:** a synthetic restaurant with a real ACP-format feed + deliberately injected drift; a real AI agent attempts the order — transacts wrong *without* the verifier, gets caught *with* it. | The story lands with zero explanation ("watch the agent get lied to; watch the truth layer catch it"); all synthetic, honest, nearly free; doubles as the storytelling arc the owner wanted. | ACCEPTED + SHIPPED AS RESHAPED (D1 2026-07-03: a SCRIPTED spec-faithful demonstration actor, not a live AI agent — the "agent gets caught" framing was banned by plan amendment 6 + machine-checked at C10; the live-agent leg was the Gemini variant the owner DECLINED 2026-07-05; status synced 2026-07-06) |
    11	| S-3 | 2026-07-02 | **Positioning frame:** "the truth layer for agentic commerce" — UC-2 = the listings domain, UC-1 = the money domain, one verifier underneath; venture story = the OSS-wedge-to-commercial-audit-layer pattern (SSL Labs → Qualys; npm-audit → Snyk). | One sentence carries both modules; answers "is a validator too small?" — the validator is the wedge, the evidence-grade audit layer is the product on top. | ACCEPTED-FOR-PLANNING (with S-1; use in plan positioning) |
    12	| S-4 | 2026-07-02 | **Process: cut review ceremony to module boundaries.** Per-slice gate = `npm run verify` green + red-green tests; the full Codex + acceptance-gate ceremony only at module boundaries and before anything irreversible. | Slice 1 spent ~1.2M shared-seat tokens across 5 Codex passes largely on wording; the owner already moved this way ("batch the Codex review") — make it standing policy for the new build. | ACCEPTED + PRACTICED (folded into plan v1.0 §5 as the S-4 module-boundary gates, owner GO 2026-07-02; run at M1/M2/Pub; status synced 2026-07-06) |
    13	| S-5 | 2026-07-02 | **Close out the suspended slice-2 diff:** commit it as-is with its honest degraded-run labels; declare the multi-agent-activation lineage CLOSED as "the spine's provenance" (capability proof); drop the clean-K live re-run — the pivot doesn't need it. | Converts a dangling obligation into the credibility exhibit the new build stands on; frees the repo for the restructure. | ACCEPTED + DONE (executed as S0 at the owner GO — slice-2 provenance close-out committed `a65064b`, 2026-07-02; status synced 2026-07-06) |
    14	| S-6 | 2026-07-02 | **Edge-case coverage = an enumerated taxonomy with measured eval coverage** (drift types × fee tactics × encoding × availability races × spec-version skew), never an "all edge cases" claim. | "All" is an overclaim our honesty rules forbid; enumerated + measured is stronger — it's provable. | ACCEPTED (standing directive c, decision-log 2026-07-02) |
    15	| S-7 | 2026-07-02 | **Demo-agent honesty guardrail:** the agent that "gets caught" is a demonstration actor — scripted/simulated (labeled) or Gemini-driven within the $5 cap — never Claude/Codex as product runtime. | Preserves the RULES §8 dev-tools-are-not-the-product line before the demo design starts, not after. | ACCEPTED (standing directive d, decision-log 2026-07-02) |
    16	| S-8 | 2026-07-02 | **Documentation frameworks as the floor:** Diátaxis (doc architecture) · Minto Pyramid/SCQA (summaries + narrative; resonance from story structure, never hype) · C4 model (architecture visuals; context level = the lay view) · two-register principle + glossary. | Grounds the owner's "document like a professional" directive in named, verifiable methodologies instead of taste. | ACCEPTED (`docs/documentation-standard.md`, decision-log 2026-07-02) |
    17	| S-9 | 2026-07-02 | **The product's own output IS a document:** the drift/audit report a merchant or platform engineer receives must itself meet the documentation standard — professional terminology, evidence attached, one readable page, a visual, a plain-words summary line per finding. | The documentation discipline and product quality converge in the report; designing it in from the start beats retrofitting. | ACCEPTED + IMPLEMENTED (W3 one-page `/report` + machine JSON, per-finding `plainLine`, legibility as hard constraint; M1 SHIP 2026-07-03; status synced 2026-07-06) |
    18	| S-10 | 2026-07-02 | **Legibility as concrete artifact constraints:** one-command validator · one-page drift report · a demo that needs no explanation — "complexity spent inside, simplicity delivered outside." | Turns the owner's "not complex outwards" intent into testable design requirements. | ACCEPTED (standing directive b, decision-log 2026-07-02) |
    19	
    20	| S-11 | 2026-07-02 | **Product name recommendation: "Assay"** (the independent test of what's claimed — gold assaying; maker≠judge in one word; CLI-native: `assay check feed.json`; tagline "Assay — the truth layer for agentic commerce"). Alternates in order: Parallax · Tare · Trig · Plumbline · Kilter. Naming principles applied: 1–2 syllables, concrete truth-semantics, CLI-usable, domain-neutral across both modules, no category clichés (no Veri-/Truth-/-ify/AI suffixes). Killed-for-collision but conceptually noted: Tally (split tally-stick; tally.so), Expo (kitchen expeditor; expo.dev), Galley (galley proof; Galley food-data co), Hawk-Eye (keep as pitch analogy only). **All collision notes are UNVERIFIED-from-memory — a live trademark/domain/npm/GitHub check is REQUIRED before adoption (RULES §6); name confirm = owner-gated stop.** LIVE SCREEN RAN at the Pub gate (2026-07-06): **"Assay" COLLIDED** — assay.tools is a live 2026 AI-agent devtools product (same broad space) and bare npm `assay` is squatted (abandoned 2013); alternates not fully screened (seat limits; labeled UNVERIFIED). Interim: the repo publishes under the DESCRIPTIVE name "Commerce Truth Audit" (not a brand adoption — this gate stays open). **FULL ALTERNATES SCREEN RAN LIVE (2026-07-06, fourteenth session — npm registry + GitHub handles + product web search; domains + trademark NOT checked, still required pre-adoption): Parallax = KILLED** (GradientHQ/parallax, live distributed-AI-inference devtool, #1 Product Hunt Oct 2025 + Parallax Worlds, funded AI-robotics startup + parall.ax AI consultancy — same/adjacent space) · **Trig = KILLED** (trig.ai, live London AI-agent platform, $10.3M raised — same space) · **Tare = RISKY** (Tare, live NY AI email-marketing startup for Shopify merchants, funded 2023, LinkedIn `tare-ai` — commerce-AI adjacent) · **Kilter = DILUTED but no same-space product** (Blackbaud-acquired wellness app 2022 + Kilter Systems agtech robots + Kilterly CS SaaS; bare npm/GitHub taken-stale) · **Plumbline = CLEANEST** (no live software product of that exact name found in AI/devtools/commerce; bare npm = stale 2022 Angular test util; github.com/plumbline taken; scoped `@plumbline/…` npm available as with all candidates). Ranked for the pick: **Plumbline > Kilter**; Tare risky; Parallax/Trig/Assay dead. **Plumbline DOMAIN screen ran live 2026-07-07 (capabilities sweep):** still no same-space software product found (nearest: “Plumb,” an AI-automation tool, shut down 2025-10-31), **but every natural exact-match domain is REGISTERED** (plumbline.com/.dev/.io/.ai + getplumbline.com all resolve; several look parked, none an active same-space product) — an adoption would need a variant domain (e.g. plumbline-audit / the scoped npm `@plumbline/…`, which is available) or a different name. USPTO trademark check still UNVERIFIED (needs a proper TESS query — not reliably doable from this environment). **CLOSED 2026-07-12 (S7 wording sync, plan v3.3):** the owner adopted **"Curbside Commons"** (2026-07-08 amendment word; diligence record `docs/s11-curbside-commons-diligence.md`, clean on every authoritative check) as the **final non-commercial display brand — no clearance claimed**; the candidates in this row are history. Terminology note: the USPTO's current system is **Trademark Search** (tmsearch.uspto.gov; TESS retired — live-checked 2026-07-12); the owner tails (register `curbsidecommons.com` · manual USPTO Trademark Search query before any ® /™ claim, none made) remain open owner acts. | CLOSED (final non-commercial display brand "Curbside Commons", no clearance claimed — S7 2026-07-12; owner tails open: domain registration + manual USPTO Trademark Search) |
    21	
    22	**Maintenance:** every new independent suggestion gets a row here in the same breath it's made; status updated when the owner reacts or a gate rules. Statuses here never substitute for the decision-log — consequential acceptances always get their decision-log row.
    23	
    24	**⚠ Coherence note (2026-07-02, post-council+Codex):** S-1's "no conformance tooling exists" premise and S-3's "truth layer" identity are SUPERSEDED by the research CORRECTION (official `ucp-schema` validator exists; category language diluting) and the council+Codex reshape: identity = mechanism-led ("we check the feed against reality"), "truth layer" = tagline only; the lead-artifact framing is now governed by `docs/plan-truth-audit-execution.md` (UC-1 = primary evidence/AI track; UC-2 = bounded frontier demo pending the pre-build crux gate). S-1/S-3 statuses unchanged as history; do not build from their text.

