The header values and Cloudflare rule shape look appropriate for this static site, but the binding test has a concrete adversarial seam: it converts header pairs into an object before asserting equality. That collapses duplicate names, so “exactly four headers” is not actually enforced if a fifth line repeats an adopted name. I’m validating that against the intended policy and checking whether any higher-severity issue exists before classifying it.
