   585	  <!-- ============================== #evidence ============================= -->
   586	  <section id="evidence" aria-labelledby="evidence-h2">
   587	    <div class="sec-inner">
   588	      <div class="sec-head reveal">
   589	        <p class="eyebrow"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#ic-spark"/></svg> Labels are earned here, or not claimed</p>
   590	        <h2 class="h2" id="evidence-h2">Every quality label traces to a pre-registered run.</h2>
   591	        <p class="prose">Floors are committed in git before any run; splits are burned after one scoring pass; misses stay on the record. The eval evidence dashboard traces every figure to its committed record.</p>
   592	      </div>
   593	      <ul class="cards c3" role="list">
   594	        <li class="card reveal" data-stagger="0">
   595	          <div class="card-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><use href="#ic-check"/></svg></div>
   596	          <p class="kicker">Fee-line classifier</p>
   597	          <p class="stat-figure">21/21</p>
   598	          <p class="stat-note">The first calibration run missed one floor and the label was <em>deferred</em> &mdash; that record stays public. A fresh pre-registered retry then cleared every floor and earned it.</p>
   599	        </li>
   600	        <li class="card reveal" data-stagger="60">
   601	          <div class="card-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><use href="#ic-person"/></svg></div>
   602	          <p class="kicker">Agent-crew live run</p>
   603	          <p class="stat-figure">20/20</p>
   604	          <p class="stat-note">Scored against floors committed before the run &mdash; and only the two model-directed members carry the &ldquo;agent&rdquo; label, because that is what the pre-registration licenses.</p>
   605	        </li>
   606	        <li class="card reveal" data-stagger="120">
   607	          <div class="card-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><use href="#ic-alert"/></svg></div>
   608	          <p class="kicker">The lanes that missed</p>
   609	          <p class="stat-figure deferred">Floors not met &mdash; and it says so</p>
   610	          <p class="stat-note">Two enhancement lanes (retrieval, entity resolution) missed their pre-registered floors: both labels defer, on every payload, and the full scoreboards stay published. Deferral is a feature.</p>
   611	        </li>
   612	      </ul>
   613	    </div>
   614	  </section>
